  "studyName": "Mapping Systemic Lupus Erythematosus heterogeneity at the single cell level",
  "tables": [
    {
      "tableName": "SLE_Subject_Phenotypes",
      "datasetId": "pht010316.v1",
      "description": "This subject phenotypes data table informs of subject's case or control status for Systemic Lupus Erythematosus (SLE), self-reported sex, race, ethnicity, and age, whether the subject is healthy or has SLE, the batch in which the subject samples were sequenced, the year when subject provided blood sample, subject's Systemic Lupus Erythematosus Disease Activity Index (SLEDAI score), subject's preliminary criteria of global flare for childhood-onset SLE from the MD provider. It also containsfrom SLEDAI 2K Assessment form: arthritis score, rash score, proteinuria score, hematuria score, urinary casts score (points), pyuriva score, increased DNA binding score, low complement score, fever score, pleurisy, vasculitis score, alopecia score, Leukopenia score; whether Mycophenolic acid drug, oral steroid, methotrexate drug, and /or plaquenil are present in the subject's blood sample, subject's history of nephritis, the presence or absence of proliferative nephritis and membranous nephritis in the subject, subject's nephrology class, subject's numerous variables based on Nephrology class, subject's erythrocyte sedimentation rate, subject's whole blood cell count, subject's red blood cell count, subject's monocyte percentage, neutrophil percentage, lymphocyte percentage, hemoglobin levels, hematocrit, platelet count, neutrophil count, lymphocyte count, creatinine level, albumin level, double stranded DNA ratio and level, complement C3 and C4 level, Alanine Transaminase level, Aspartate Aminotransferase level, Aldosterone level, and Lactate dehydrogenase level, presence or absence of muscular skeletal rash or arthritis in the subject, from SLEDAI score in the subject: presence or absence of proteinuria, casts, pyuria, hematuria, presence or absence of dsDNA and low complement.",
